  "prompt": "My username is no longer available on Skype. Why?",
  "response": "There are a few common reasons why your username might no longer be available on Skype:\n\n*   **Account Deletion:** If you haven't used your Skype account for an extended period, Skype might have automatically deleted it due to inactivity. This is a measure they take to clean up their database.\n\n*   **Account Closure:** You (or someone with access to your account) may have closed your Skype account. Once an account is closed, the username typically becomes unavailable for re-registration.\n\n*   **Username Taken by Someone Else:** It's possible that after your account was deleted (due to inactivity or closure), someone else created a new account using your old username. This can happen as Skype allows for username reuse in certain circumstances.\n\n*   **Technical Issue:** While less likely, there could be a temporary glitch or problem with Skype's system that is preventing the username from being recognized.\n\nHere are some troubleshooting steps and things to consider:\n\n*   **Try to Sign In:** Attempt to sign in to Skype using your old username and password. If you can't remember the password, try the \"Forgot Password\" recovery option. This will help determine if the account still exists.\n*   **Check for Account Closure Confirmation:** If you remember closing your account, check your email for any confirmation messages from Skype. This will confirm that the account was indeed closed.\n*   **Contact Skype Support:** If you are unable to recover the account or find any information about its status, reach out to Skype Support directly. They can investigate the issue and provide more specific details about why your username is unavailable.\n\nWhen contacting Skype Support, be prepared to provide as much information as possible about your account, such as:\n\n*   Your old Skype username\n*   The email address associated with the account\n*   Any phone numbers linked to the account\n*   Any billing information you might have used for Skype services\n\n**Important Note:** Skype has transitioned away from usernames as the primary identifier for accounts. They now use email addresses or phone numbers. If you're creating a new Skype account, you'll need to use one of these.\n\nGood luck getting this resolved!",
